        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 8 at 2:37PM CDT by NWS Mobile AL</headline>
        <description>At 237 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Red Level, or 11 miles northwest of Andalusia, moving southeast at 30
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Andalusia, Opp, River Falls, Red Level, Heath, and Gantt.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
